**Item #:** SCP-6914

**Object Class:** --Euclid-- Pending

**Special Containment Procedures:** All previous procedures have been halted pending further investigation.

**Description:** SCP-6914 is a grandfather clock, heavily modified. The face has been replaced with a round digital display, although it still ticks as normal.

Periodically, SCP-6914 will chime, before displaying a name, date and time. It will continue to show this information until the named individual dies, invariably at the cited time, at which point it will chime again and switch off. These events take place seemingly at random, with a maximum recorded time of five years and nine months between one prediction taking place and the next being made. Predictions have been made for anywhere between two years and seven minutes in the future. All matching deaths have occurred in Britain.

All attempts to prevent or otherwise alter these events have failed.

**Addendum 15:** Notable cases.

> **Victim:** Sofia Delgado
> 
> 
> **Time of death:** 12/01/1999, 2:03 PM
> 
> 
> **Notes:** This being the first event to occur under containment, SCP-6914’s effect was not fully understood. As such, identification and retrieval was deemed only a moderate priority, and Delgado was not located until after the due time, at which point she had died from alcoholic liver disease in Blackpool Victoria Hospital, Lancashire.

> **Victim:** Ülkü İbrahimoğlu
> 
> 
> **Time of death:** 23/10/2002, 10:42 PM
> 
> 
> **Notes:** İbrahimoğlu was the first victim successfully contacted prior to the event after several failed attempts, typically due to the victim's name being too common in the region to specify. Two hours before the event, he was contacted, informed that his life was in danger and instructed to stay in his home. MTF Zeta-20 ("Flag Snaggers") was dispatched and arrived with twenty-seven minutes to spare, with orders to guard İbrahimoğlu until the due time had passed.
> 
> 
> While there, [REDACTED][[footnote]]Because it cannot be determined whether the individual was negligent or unconsciously influenced by a poorly-understood anomaly, name has been withheld.[[/footnote]] lit a cigarette by a gas stove that had been left on, leading to a chain of events culminating in İbrahimoğlu being trapped in the resulting conflagration with Agent Shaughnessy. The agent made a full recovery despite smoke inhalation and second-degree burns, but İbrahimoğlu died at the scene.

> **Victim:** Valerie Whitaker
> 
> 
> **Time of death:** 07/02/1933, 11:20 AM
> 
> 
> **Notes:** [DATA EXPUNGED]

> **Victim:** ███████ McIver
> 
> 
> **Time of death:** 20/12/2021, 12:08 AM
> 
> 
> **Notes:** McIver was located six months prior to her time of death. Given that this was the first opportunity for long-term study, she was fully informed of SCP-6914 and its anomalous properties, and agreed to participate in interviews and testing, as well as relocate to Site 135 a week before the due time.[[footnote]]McIver requested that the Foundation not inform her of the exact date and time; this was deemed acceptable.[[/footnote]] At time of writing, she remains under observation. Researcher Farnsworth has been designated her Foundation liason.
